step.tex:
\begin{align}
\int \left(\sqrt x +\dfrac{1}{\sqrt x}\right)dx &= \int x^{\dfrac{1}{2}}dx  + \int x^{-\dfrac{1}{2}}dx\\
														&= \dfrac{x^{\dfrac{1}{2} +1}}{\left(\dfrac{1}{2}+1\right)} + \dfrac{x^{-\dfrac{1}{2}+1}}{\left(-\dfrac{1}{2}+1\right)}+ C\\                    
														&= \dfrac{2}{3}x^{\dfrac{3}{2}} + 2x^{\dfrac{1}{2}} + C\\
\end{align}	\\
\text{Here, C is the constant of integration}
